servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb} until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add garlic and half the minced ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @jasmine rice{½%cup}, ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Trout ==

While rice cooks, pat @steelhead trout{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Swap in trout for chicken; add to pan skin sides down.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium-high heat. Add trout and cook until skin is crispy, ~{5-6%minutes}. Flip and cook until opaque and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} more.

Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside. Wipe out pan.

== Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in same pan over medium heat. Add scallion whites and remaining minced ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant and softened, ~{1%minute}.

Add @miso sauce concentrate{1}, half the @apricot jam{1} (all for 4 servings), ¼ cup water (1/3 cup for 4), and a squeeze of lime juice to pan with aromatics. Cook, stirring, until combined and thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Taste and add more lime juice if desired.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt.

Toss carrots with lime zest.

Divide rice, carrots, and trout between plates. Drizzle trout with sauce and sprinkle everything with scallion greens. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.